EDIT: changed from 1 stars to 3 stars after the owner reached out to us offering a refund/gift card. The owner seems genuinely kind and perhaps this was just a one off experience. It’s hard to be a restaurant operating during covid  One of the worst dining experiences I’ve had in awhile. We went for dinner. We all ordered a round of cocktails and not a single person enjoyed theirs with 4 of the cocktails missing entire ingredients. The cocktails were $12-$15 and tasted like I overpaid for them at a nightclub. The food was cold and made us all feel a bit ill afterwards. Two people in our party ordered the steak and were not asked how they wanted it cooked. When they tracked down staff to ask for a medium rare steak, they said their default was medium well. What kind of restaurant never asks how you want your steak cooked and then defaults to medium well?? We paid an extra $4 for our pasta to have chicken and not only was that inedible but there were approximately 2 pieces in it. The mushroom flatbread wasn’t even on par with the frozen Trader Joe’s one. My party travelled 30 minutes to come here and we were intensely disappointed. When we asked for the manager they weren’t even on the premises and we had to argue with the staff about how bad both the food and drinks were only to be told we must have a “different palate”. In the end we did not have to pay for drinks and got half the food compensated, but to be honest that took way too much arguing and we probably shouldn’t have had to pay at all. And I forgot to mention the drinks didn’t come for 45 minutes and the food didn’t come for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

Really disappointing!  I booked a table in advance and two people in my party were a little late and the host wouldn’t let us sit even though you have 90 mins from your reservation start time.  The table was not ready even though they made us wait.  The hostess was incredibly rude to my friends for no reason. The first thing she said was “We are not accepting walk-ins right now” with a really condescending attitude before I even said anything. I told her I already had a reservation but my friend is running a few minutes late but we would like to sit and order. She made us wait on the sidewalk until my friend came. This whole wait rule is ridiculous especially since you have 90 mins from the reservation time. What are they accomplishing exactly by making people wait for their whole party? The hostess was also not wearing a mask the whole time.  The food was good but not worth the price and the menu had a very limited selection.  If you want mimosas, you order a bottle of champagne and pay extra for Orange juice. You’ll get a single small cup with literally two fingers of juice.  The champagne “glasses” are made of plastic that went through multiple wars and looks barely washed. The utensils aren’t much better.  The servers were really nice and helpful and wore masks the whole time, which is why I still tipped 20% despite the horrible hostess.  Overall, waste of a Sunday brunch!

I will try and keep it simple: The food was very good in my one experience but my review refers to the way I was treated. Note: we are in quarantine times for those reading, so it was a weird time.  My gf and I ordered food online. There was a great deal--an app, 2 entrees (talkin them Eric Entrees) and a dessert. I had been craving wings for a week so I chose wings as the appetizer. When I arrived to pick up my food, the front-of-house employee says they are out of wings--would I like to choose another appetizer? I was irritated at first. They called my gf while she was driving and so she did not pick up the phone but they tried to let us know. I did not know this, so I chose the nachos -- with chicken added-- even though there is an up charge for chicken. He said he could only give me the nachos without the chicken and I argued that since I paid for wings, the up-charged-nachos still cost less than the wings I paid for.  Well you see, I was very hungry and had forgotten that I actually bought a bundle deal. I didn't pay for "wings"--I paid for an appetizer. And the base appetizer you get when you order nachos does not come with chicken. I was technically in the wrong to argue for my chicken to be added free of charge but the man obliged. I realized the mistake I made when we drove away and felt like a jerk but it made the fact that they gave me what I asked for on a day when things were clearly weird for them mean a lot more. I now have a loyalty to Hutch and will at least be back again to try the wings! I really appreciate them giving me the benefit of the doubt in my time of hunger. When this world opens back up from quarantine, I can't wait to stop in for a couple of beers. They got my loyalty.

We were lucky enough to come on half priced bottled wine night, which is always a plus. The Impossible burger and chicken sandwich were perfect AND, most importantly, we received absolutelu perfect service from Laura. She was an absolute joy. We couldn't have picked a better place to spend our Thursday night in town.
Is it even possible to have a bad experience at Hutch?! Great service, delicious food and wonderful ambiance. One of our go-to brunch spots 👏🏻
Great decor. Average cuisine. High priced. Mediocre service. Acted like he was intimidated by us. Good thing we had a groupon.

We used to go to Hutch weekly for brunch or dinner, and was great for the big groups of 6-12 that we brought.  The past 3 out of 4 times left everyone saying they don’t care to return.  Servers and bartenders seemed disinterested, and 3 of the 10 meals were not as asked.  They only offered to ‘make it right,’ but instead of comping anything they brought replacements after others were done eating.  It’s sad though.  This used to be everyone’s go-to, but now that has passed.   Please make it top notch like it used to.

Guys, why do we keep doing it. Hutch is consistently average. For the diner-esque brunch food they serve, there's so many other places that do it better or the same for less. I get that there's great beverage deals but it's not enough to justify it.
Best breakfast!
Good food and coffee. I'd be back for a boozy brunch
Really good biscuit and chicken!
Good atmosphere, great for brunch
Worth going for the cheesy potatoes alone.

Didn’t love my experience there. First of all, they had everyone waiting outside for 10 minutes after they were supposed to open. Then, the food that I ordered was bland. Most people at the table felt that the food was overpriced and under-seasoned. The prices are just too high for the quality of the food not being the best.
Very cozy and quaint:) food and service was awesome!

Slightly over priced food, but the food is good. Happy hour and drink specials are on going and they can make a great drink!! I recommend this place if you are celebrating or not worried about money. Super friendly staff and chill atmosphere.

I came here for brunch on a Sunday mostly because Bloody Mary's were advertised as an $8.00 brunch special. Upon receipt of my bloody mary, I realized there was a hair stuck to the salami. I politely asked the server for a new bloody mary. She came back with presumably the same bloody Mary with the hair removed from the salami. This time there was a hair stuck to the toothpick going inside the drink. At this point it wasnt worth asking for a new one because it was evident the hair was being removed behind the scenes and I was not being given a new drink. Come on, do a better job of violating health standards. I left the drink untouched the remainder of the meal and the server never inquired about it. We came to find out this hairy bloody mary was $10.00 instead of $8.00. Talk about several disappointments.
Above average, pleasant restaurant.  Be sure to check the menu in advance.  Limited choices.
Really good burger. The setup makes it a bit messy. Get it without the setup (lettuce, tomato, pickle)
Dude, the best.  I love this place already but seamus rocked the shot today.  Come here,for all your week day brunch needs.  And mimosas.  And great food,

I've come here twice now - once for dinner and once for brunch, and I have been greatly pleased with the bright atmosphere and food both times.  Hutch is an excellent venue for an outing in Wrigleyville with friendly service and reasonable prices.
Disappointing.
Good fun, fun place
Delicious endless mimosas with many flavors to choose from. Great stop to people watch!
Not a bad brunch, but the cocktails are better than the food.
Good food cool atmosphere nice patio and great daily specials.  Food pretty rich but delicious
Yummy and fun
To start with the customer service is outstanding. Next the food is prepared to perfection and they have a great wine selection
Great drinks. Solid food. Good date spot. Or spot to show friends who visit the neighborhood.
got the porkchops and husband got the fish and chips. porkchops were delish! the fish were very small but the fries it came with were delicious!
Perfect spot for breakfast!
Great food, great service. Very busy place, with good reason.

I stopped in for their weekday brunch and could not have been more impressed with the food, drinks, and hospitality! At $3 each, their weekday mimosa deal cannot be beat. I cannot wait to return to check out their weekend brunch experience!

We stumbled upon this place while looking for a restaurant in Lincoln Square. It was lovely. The ambiance is quaint and charming, and the service was absolutely wonderful.  My only complaint - and I can't believe I'm typing this - is that the portions were a bit too big. I ordered the Amish chicken, and my companion ordered the pork loin. Both were big enough to have been shared. (And, we have big appetites, generally).  The star of the evening was the burrata appetizer! Superb!

Place was busy on Sunday, which is good for business. However this was first for me to pay $14.50 for one bagel and lox?!!  Was served  glass with lipsticks on it, and  plate which was dirty as well. Two stars for pleasant waitress. Not looking forward to go back.
Great brunch, great atmosphere although it was quite loud
Great restaurant, great food, they took extra care of us because they were a little short staffed, great customer service!

I'm a vegetarian who stupidly missed the word "chorizo" from the item I ordered at brunch. After my sandwich arrived and I saw the meat, I sheepishly asked the server about this and let her know that I was in fact a vegetarian and wouldn't be able to eat it ... she was very understanding and had a new one made and brought over in minutes. This was totally my fault and they didn't bat an eye - so, GREAT service! Also, the food and drinks were excellent - we'll definitely be back.
Open at 5pm, not convenient especially for a late lunch or early dinner.
Average food
Lobster nachos were great
The non-alcoholic drinks are quite pricy with no refills if you aren’t a drinker and the wait staff is hard to find throughout your meal.
Best restaurant I have been to in many years! Service is top notch and the menu is amazing! Brunch is off the charts!

Came for Monday brunch, the covered patio was perfect! Food was great as always and service was friendly and attentive. Great brunch drink specials too! Whenever I need a weekday brunch, Hutch is the first place I go to and has never disappointed.
Incredibly delicious food and excellent service!
Best pictures of China cabinets on the wall. Best 90's dance music play list.
Crackel  Brarrel feel with a spice.
Very good service, great drinks

Best brunch place in Wrigleyville! Nutella poppers are to die for. Ask for their blood orange mimosas for brunch as well! Make sure to reserve spots online for brunch as there is usually a long wait time.

Gotta love food poisoning! Was there just this past Sunday and myself and two others who were there came down with food poisoning. Food definitely isn’t good enough to risk feeling this way EVER again.
Great brunch spot here! Amazing options and everything tasted great. Be sure to make a reservation!

We were pretty fortunate to be able to find a table for five for a Sunday brunch without a wait. They were packed, but we timed it just right.  Hutch American Bistro was a little understaffed but our server was fantastic. I wish I recall his name now but we made sure to let the manager know how accommodating he was. They have a decent selection and I decided I would try their breakfast burrito.  After a short wait (it was crowded), we were served. The burrito was good but not outstanding. It was smaller than others served. The eggs were good and I do admit the Chorizo was very well prepared. The fruit they served with it was a little underripe. Other than the fruit, I really enjoyed the brunch.  And, again, I only wish I could remember the server's name or I would call him out so you could ask for him when you go.
Staff very helpful and the food is good
Good Food
Overrated food. Better spots for the price in the neighborhood.

This place is amazing! I went with my fiance on the day of Pride and the place was predictably packed, but the restaurant was appropriately stocked and staffed to handle the crowd. Amidst the chaos we were able to take a seat at the bar and were served in an extremely timely and friendly manner. Not to mention the food was delicious- their fries are out of this world!
Just had beers this time, but I'm trying the Lobster nachos when I go back.

5 star Service staff is amazing, always accommodating of large parties for brunch early in the day on the weekends. They will help split large checks too but make sure you give them plenty of notice. Food is good for brunch, but they revamped their menu a bit and a few favorites are gone. Bummed that they got rid of the shrimp and grits, it was one of my favorites. The pulled bacon is delish, definitely recommend that too.
The dips(hummus spinach and artichoke) were fine yet the chops felt poor quality and stale. Just cut up  the wonderful flat breads and sevre that
Two words: pulled bacon.
Great comfortable space, friendly atmosphere & wise range of great items to choose from on the menu. Totally recommended!

We were pretty fortunate to be able to find a table for five for a Sunday brunch without a wait. They were packed, but we timed it just right.  Hutch American Bistro was a little understaffed but our server was fantastic. I wish I recall his name now but we made sure to let the manager know how accommodating he was. They have a decent selection and I decided I would try their breakfast burrito.  After a short wait (it was crowded), we were served. The burrito was good but not outstanding. It was smaller than others served. The eggs were good and I do admit the Chorizo was very well prepared. The fruit they served with it was a little underripe. Other than the fruit, I really enjoyed the brunch.  And, again, I only wish I could remember the server's name or I would call him out so you could ask for him when you go.

We eat here regularly, and it is always a great experience. The back waiters in particular are terrific, and see to it that everyone has what they needs. They've cleaned up the menu a bit and I think it's an improvement, back to basics. Standouts on the menu for me are the pork chop as an entree and the meatballs as an appetizer, but you can't really go wrong here. Bar is fun as well but it is small and often packed, but the dining room is spacious.

Went here before a baseball game got there an hour and 10 before the start of the game had to wait a hour and a half and never got food. Our waiter vanished and we're told multiple times that our food was coming right up.  When we finally left we were told that the kitchen is understaffed on a Sunday night before a baseball game.  Am very disappointed, and will never be back. If you do decide to go here before a game I would recommend getting there two hour before time but I don't know if that is enough.  No idea about the food, it could be good, never got to try it.

I ordered the waffle, but asked for ice cream and strawberries on the side. This waffle was one of the BEST I've ever had! The other food at the table was wonderful, as well, but that waffle....WOW! Service was excellent, prices were fair.
Beer was cold, food was awesome and the service first notch, would definitely go back.
Thanks for doing what you can to save the environment by becoming a straw-free restaurant!
Food is good. Drinks are strong. Great ambiance. Can get crowded. Needs larger selection on menu.

What a super spot for brunch. We went en route to Wrigley. The food was awesome. Great portions, and delicious items. The potato casserole was really yummy. There variety of drinks were great, and the carafe option for mimosas is very reasonably priced. It gets busy on game day! We sat at the bar and got great recommendations for where to go next from them! Would definitely go back.
The best mimosas I have ever had! And mash potatoes!
I like this place. They have good cocktails and a decent menu of mostly brunch and breakfast items. It's reliable and the service is usually excellent.
always good food not too pricy
Thier mimosas are awesome, thier brunch game is on POINT. it gets very busy during brunch on Sunday so call for a reservation.
Sat at the bar and overall experience was fantastic. Great bartenders and great food. One of the best bloody Mary's I've ever had.
Delicious food, very busy.
Good food and service
A little expensive for brunch places surrounding area
Love everything except the cramped seating.
Good breakfast/ brunch spot in a great location. Food was good,  service was not. I've only been once and would probably try it again

We had brunch there on a Saturday morning and it was packed! The acoustic is pretty bad so it was hard to hear people in my party of 4! Having said that, the food was great and the service was good. Food came pretty fast and our waiter was very attentive.
Over priced, very small portions of not very good food.  Service was good though
Had a delicious Easter brunch there
Great place! Had the pulled pork sandwich. Glad to hear they added a location in Andersonville.
Good
Absolutely amazing menu, friendly staff, and got us in during busy brunch without a wait.
Good food with good service. Quality menu with lots of different options and styles of dish.
Good atmosfery but the taste of the food and coffee really wasn't special. Salad for $12 was pretty small...
Great breakfast, loved the ice cream and waffle, who knew it would be that delicious!
Fantastic brunch.  They do not take reservations though, so get there before 11:00 or risk a line.
Love! Absolutely amazing cheesy potatoes and mimosas

We waited 10 minutes for the server to talk to us and we didn't get our drinks until we were halfway done with the food. The food itself was fine but nothing special. Overall not worth the hour+ wait for the table.
Proportions are definitely lacking, combined with understaffed service.  The food almost makes it worth it

Great food and friendly staff. The bistro has a fun, bright, open vibe. The eggs Benedict were amazing. The cheesy potatoes are out of this world. There's a nice selection of drinks and mimosas on the menu. Serving sizes are in hearty portions. Good for a brunch date, or a family/group outing.

Went for brunch, and the price you pay is exactly what you end up getting. I would steer away from conventional burgers, although fries were amazing, and stick to the big biscuit with friend chicken, amazing!

We absolutely loved Hutch! We went for brunch and food was amazing to say the least. I had the Belgium waffle with vanilla icecream and strawberries (mind was blown), my fiancé had the chicken and waffles (also tasty)! We decided to try the pulled bacon, definitely did not disappoint. Ordered a carafe of mimosas (huge variety of fresh juices to mix with, we had blood orange) for $16, great deal (about 8 glasses)! Our server Shamus also made our experience great, he was awesome while we asked a bunch of questions, and got everything out quick with a smile. Highly recommend, we can’t wait to return!
Very food food and terrific service. Nice variety of breakfast choices, from Mexican to Jewish to American. Portions are pretty good sized so none will leave hungry.
Great food, nice atmosphere. Bartender and staff were great.
Best avocado chicken toast I've had! With the egg on top!!! 😋
Food was amazing. Waiter was a jerk
Best burgers
Skillet came out looking like a soup. The waiter was great and kindly offered a new dish.
Wonderful atmosphere!  Food is delicious and reasonably priced. Thoroughly enjoyed our brunching experience. I highly recommend to visitors to Chicago and locals.
Great food
Came here for brunch and it was delicious!
New bistro. Good start, has a few bugs but once they work them out I can say it will be a great addition to Andersonville.
I left hungry :( otherwise it tasted good.
Good brunch place, American food,l. No complaints.
Decent food. Friendly staff. Exotic options. Not the best place for traditional breakfast fare.
Crowded but good drinks
Good spot to eat drink and unwind with friends
One of my favorite brunch spots in Chicago
Great food. Quiet and intimate.

My husband and I just recently moved to Chicago and unfortunately this was the first restaurant to disappoint us. The restaurant wasn't busy at all, maybe 6 tables were set so we figured the service and food would be quick but we were …
Our 4th time here (twice for Valentine's specials). Food was very good and service was very helpful and friendly. Certainly recommend Hutch if you've never eaten here.

Mostly American fare. But the fish tacos are great. Outside seating in season. They close fairly early, even on week ends. Normally no wait for a table, except on game day/night, especially if the Cubs are hot. Sunday brunch gets crowded. Valet parking available, though I don’t know where they put the cars.
Great place to get brunch. Plus their mimosas pitchers are great for groups
Great dinner specials and the staff is terrific.
Food and service top notch. Always have a reservation!
10 dollar mimosa pitcher during the weekdays. Enough said. The great food is a bonus!

The staff was friendly and extremely busy. The restaurants location in between Boystown and Wrigleyville makes for an interesting mix of people. The food was mediocre, it didn't change my life but I also wasn't disgusted while eating. The best thing we did was order the Nutella poppers - deep fried Nutella filled dough, I mean, how can that go wrong?
Grat spot for brunch and mimosas! They have all kinds of different mimosas available in carafes. The nutella bites are ridiculously good too. Get there early to get a seat!
The equivalent of a four-star hotel: nice, but not amazing.
The bartender (Mora) is amazing. The food is great,and the drinks are better. Great spot for brunch
Good service and food and drinks.
Great food, very well chosen  wines, innovative cocktails and very welcoming ambience.

We were visiting from Canada and came for brunch based on a recommendation from a friend who knew the city. Coming from Toronto, where we love our brunches, we were not disappointed.  We got lucky with the weather and were able to enjoy the sunshine on the patio. Our server was practically a sunbeam herself, was very personable, put us into great mood, and talked us into the large carafe of mimosas. A gentleman at the table next to us overhead me ordering the Big Biscuit and Fried Chicken, and interrupted us to say it was one of the best new things he'd had in years. Again, I was not disappointed, it was one of my favourite meals from our entire trip. My partner is still talking about the Totchos he had as well. We're going to try to make them both, but replicating them will be a challenge! If they ever open shop in Toronto we'll be there on opening day.

Went for a bite with a friend. It wasn’t very crowded at 8 on a Thursday so we were seated right away. The atmosphere was great for catching up with a friend but would probably be good for a date as well. It wasn’t too dark or loud so it was easy to have a conversation.  The cocktails were tasty and inexpensive but not very strong. And there was an interesting selection.  I ordered the fish tacos and they were fine, nothing to rave about but still good. The fries though were very good, I couldn’t stop eating them. I was surprised that they were thinly cut and crispy because most of the places I’ve been to recently have slightly thicker fries. These were perfect.
Great food.
Made a reservation on OpenTable the night before for 11:30 brunch on a Sunday. Got right in and we’re seated immediately. No long wait for anything. Food was amazing and the mimosas are strong 👌🏻
Quick service. Rotating draft taps. Great burgers, decent entrees. Nice local next to Wrigley. Definitely not disappointed.

The food here is great and you'll realize it once you see the big lines. Only downside to me is they don't open until 10am - which to me is a bit late for 'breakfast'. The potato casserole thingy is AMAZING and comes with most plates.
Nice neighborhood spot. Good food. Great brunch option!
Great food, service was slightly slow.

Used to be our go to spot but food quality has dropped substantially  Used to have a great short rib  Now the food is mostly frozen Assuming that is why wait staff never asks if food was ok  If you go, avoid spinach and artichoke and black bean burger
Nice atmosphere delicious food!!! One of the best Benedicts in the city 👌🏻

I've been to hutch several times, but by far its brunch is the best. Really something fun and exciting and to look froward to. The options seem limitless whether you want sugary sweet or deliciously savory. The service is nice and friendly. I highly recommend making a reservation as there always seems to be a wait for brunch on the weekends. Personally, I can't wait to go back and try all of the things I didn't have last time!
